       <b> Contoso University</b> – Application Overview
        <br/>

        Contoso University is a sample web application built to demonstrate the features and best practices of a modern ASP.NET MVC application. It simulates a simple university management system and provides functionality for managing students, courses, instructors, departments, and enrollments.

        The application is  used as a teaching tool and reference project for learning ASP.NET MVC, Entity Framework, and general web development practices in the .NET ecosystem.

        🧩 Key Features

        📚 Student Management: Create, edit, and view student records.

        🧑‍🏫 Instructor Management: Assign instructors to courses and manage office assignments.

        🏫 Department Management: Handle department data and administrator assignments.

        📖 Course Enrollment: Enroll students in courses and manage grades.

        🔍 Sorting, Filtering, Paging: Easy-to-use UI for navigating large data sets.

        📊 Reporting: Simple reporting of student enrollments and course assignments.

        🛠️ Technologies Used

        ASP.NET MVC (Model-View-Controller)

        Entity Framework (Code First)

        SQL Server (LocalDB or full SQL Server)

        Bootstrap (for responsive UI)

        Razor View Engine

        🎯 Purpose

        The purpose of the Contoso University application is to serve as a reference architecture and learning project for developers working with:

        ASP.NET MVC/Web Applications

        Data access using Entity Framework

        UI development using Razor and Bootstrap

        Real-world application structure and best practices
